, "default": false, "description": "Relevant to the library team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue."}], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 4, "created_at": "2022-05-03T16:52:44Z", "updated_at": "2022-05-04T09:10:50Z", "closed_at": "2022-05-04T09:10:50Z", "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "I tried to run the following bash command using `std::process:Command`:\r\n\r\n```bash \r\nMYSQL_PWD=XXX mysql -u XXX -D XXX < file.sql\r\n```\r\nIt failed at first because I can't use `<` as an argument. Instead I had to use the `stdin` method.\r\nFrom the documentation that was not clear to me. \r\n\r\nI think the documentation should mention explicitly that redirections cannot be done with \r\n```rust\r\nCommand::new(\"mysql\")\r\n  .env(\"MYSQL_PWD\", &password)\r\n  .args([\r\n      \"-u\",\r\n      &user,\r\n      \"-D\",\r\n      &database,\r\n     \"<\",\r\n     &filename\r\n  ])\r\n```\r\nbut require\r\n```rust\r\nCommand::new(\"mysql\")\r\n  .env(\"MYSQL_PWD\", &password)\r\n  .args([\r\n      \"-u\",\r\n      &user,\r\n      \"-D\",\r\n      &database,\r\n   ])\r\n   .stdin(Stdio::from(file))\r\n```", "closed_by": {"login": "roy-ganz", "id": 42205143, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjQyMjA1MTQz", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/42205143?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/roy-ganz", "html_url": "https://github.com/roy-ganz", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/roy-ganz/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/roy-ganz/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/roy-ganz/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/roy-ganz/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/roy-ganz/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/roy-ganz/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/roy-ganz/repos", "events_